ons have largely been determined by philosophy and theology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHumiliation in literature. 0aHumility in literature. 0aModernism (Literature). 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh1 aGontarski, S. E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311078040640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147447905940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474479059423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474479059/original  a978-3-11-078040-6  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK